solution: ```class Solution {
public:
    vector<long long> maximumEvenSplit(long long finalSum) {
        vector<long long> res;
        if (finalSum % 2) return res;
        long long cur = 2;
        long long rem = finalSum;
        while (rem >= cur) {
            res.push_back(cur);
            rem -= cur;
            cur += 2;
        }
        if (rem) res.back() += rem;
        return res;
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(sqrt(finalSum))
space complexity: O(sqrt(finalSum))
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Greedy construction of the longest strictly increasing sequence of distinct even numbers starting from 2. The loop runs until the remaining sum is smaller than the next even number, then the leftover is added to the last term to keep uniqueness.

